column168: UPON INSPECTION OF TWO WET BOXES, RESPONDER DISCOVERED THESE TO BE UNDECLARED DRY ICE PACKAGES WITH CONDENSATION FORMING ON THE OUTSIDE. UPON INSPECTION OF THE INNER CONTENTS DISCOVERED APPROXIMATELY FIVE POUNDS OF DRY ICE COOLING PLANT BASED BURGERS. INNER FLAPS OF THE BOXES HAVE A RED STICKER MARKED PLANTA, CAUTION - DRY ICE - AVOID CONTACT WITH SKIN AND EYES. THESE MARKINGS WERE FOLDED INCORRECTLY SO THEY WERE ONLY VISIBLE WHEN THE BOXES WERE OPENED. THERE WERE NO VISIBLE DRY ICE MARKS OR LABELS ON THE OUTER BOXES. THERE ARE VISIBLE RED STICKERS STATING PLANTA PERISHABLE AND REFRIGERATE UPON ARRIVAL. ADDITIONAL TRACKING NUMBER TO ANOTHER CONSIGNEE IN THE USA IS 1Z25E9F10193762614.

column168: On June 2, 2023, at  1544ET, Emergency Response and Training Solutions (ERTS) was contacted by Landstar personnel in Laredo, Texas regarding a load shift in transit.  Contractors were dispatched to resecure a load of 21 1500-pound supersacks of Provox (Sodium carbonate peroxyhydrate, 5.1, II, UN3378) There was no product release during this event, and thus no waste was generated.

column168: DURING PACKAGE INSPECTION AT THE UPS FACILITY IN COLOGNE, GERMANY, TWO INNER BOXES CONTAINING CHEMICAL KIT CONTENTS WERE DISCOVERED. THERE IS NO EXCEPTED QUANTITY MARKING OR ANY OTHER DANGEROUS GOODS MARKS OR LABELS ON THE OUTERMOST BOX. THE PRODUCT IS SPECTROQUANT COD CELL TESTS. CONTENT DESCRIPTION ON THE THERMAL TRACKING LABEL AND INVOICE IS SPECTROQUANT. OUTER BOX IS A UN SPECIFICATION BOX WITH ORIENTATION ARROWS. PRIOR TO THE UNDECLARED DISCOVERY THE PACKAGE WAS FLOWN ON A UPS FLIGHT FROM VENICE, ITALY TO COLOGNE, GERMANY.
